claim.claim-text:
A heat exchanger (110) comprising a first flow circuit (111) for receiving a cold fluid (113) and a second flow circuit (112) for receiving a hot fluid (114), the first and second flow circuits having common surfaces for heat exchange, the first and second flow circuits (111, 112) each comprising a plurality of interconnected concentric annular ducts (1110-1115; 1120-1123), the two walls of each duct being mechanically decoupled from each other;

the heat exchanger presenting in the radial direction an alternating succession of pairs of adjacent annular ducts (1110, 1111; 1112, 1113; 1114, 1115) belonging to the first flow circuit (111) for the cold fluid (113) and pairs of adjacent annular ducts (1120, 1121; 1122, 1123) belonging to the second flow circuit (112) for the hot fluid (114), two adjacent annular ducts forming a distribution baffle for the cold fluid or the hot fluid;

wherein at least one side of each wall (131; 133; 135; 137; 139) common to two adjacent ducts belonging to said first or to said second flow circuit (111; 112) includes a layer of thermal insulation (122; 123; 124; 125; 126).
